name: 1.2 Cinepar HMI (1)
notes:
The LTM CinePAR 1200 S/E provides great versatility in all lighting applications. It operates on just 12.5 amps AC from a normal household outlet, and uses a 1200W single-ended HMI bulb (available separately) mounted in the axis of the reflector. A set of 6 optional lenses is available, to vary the beam size and intensity.

With the Very Narrow Spot lens, this light will throw beam of 1841 footcandles 2.8' in diameter from a distance of 50 feet.

With the Super Wide Flood, this light will throw a beam of 29 footcandles 50' in diamater, from the same distance.

Using a single-ended HMI lamp mounted in the axis of the reflector gives the Cinepar 1200W a powerful throw with a very tight, round beam. Head can be used with a combo AC electronic ballast or the 1200w AC magnetic ballast, available separately. Other available accessories include a 4 leaf barndoor set and filter frame.

The more leaves a barndoor set has, or the longer the leaves the more precisely the beam can be controlled.

name: 1K Arri Fresnel  (1)
notes:
The Arri 1K (1000w) Fresnel is an updated version of the Compact Series of Location Fresnels. Combining research, feedback from around the world and advances in technology, Arri has designed a series of six Fresnels with over 30 improvements for studio and location lighting. The True Blue Series has reduced weight, compact size and maximum light output. Arri's cross cooling system reduces lamp housing temperature by 25% and lens temperature by 17%. With special air channels built into the aluminum extrusion, a constant stream of air passes around the Fresnel lens and into the lamp head regardless of the tilt angle.

Bulb - EGT 1000W
120 or 240 volt use, AC or DC

This fixture will provide a 2.8' (0.9 m) diameter beam of 409 fc from a distance of 20' (6.1 m) at full spot. At full flood (same distance) it will provide a 48 fc, 20.4' (6.2 m) diameter beam. Laser-cut hexagonal safety mesh lets out more light and is tough enough to withstand location abuse.

This is a multi-purpose 1000 watt single Par Head for studio, location or remote use. Diffuse and Specular Intensifiers are available for boosting the light output, as well as different bulbs, both 3200 and 5000 Kelvin.

Combining the Specular Intensifier (2275) and a very narrow spot par bulb, a beam of 900 footcandles 4.4 x 3 feet, at a distance of 15 feet may be achieved. Using a wide flood par bulb with no intensifier will result in a beam of 52 footcandles 26 x 13.7 feet, at a distance of 15 feet.

Accepts different bulbs with built-in reflectors that disperse or internsify the light beam emitted from the head.
May be used as a hanging, grid or pipe mounted fixture, or mounted on a light stand.
Bulb may be rotated for hortizontal or vertical oval beam projection.

Bulbs - Sylvania / Osram FFS (1000W / 120V) PAR 64 Wide Flood Halogen Incandescent Lamp
            Sylvania / Osram FFN (1000W / 120V) Par 64 VNSP Lamp
